column5: Hi all,  the lake froze shore to shore last night, should be out there in 10 days or so....YEAH!

A few new Hibiscus flowers bloomed today on the deck. Going to 0 tonight. People are freaking that their pipes are going to freeze,guys and gals are running around like chickens with their heads cut off because they haven't winterized their boats yet. A lady called the shop today in a panic because her husband told her to get someone to winterize the boat as he is away. Why it's up to her is for Dr. Phil. She said it's in the garage, I told her to close the garage door for the weekend. It's calling for +10C next week. You guys can keep your cold right where it is.
This is so funny,my neighbour came over today to ask if my snow blower was ready to go(i always do her drive way) as she HAD  to be at work for 10 am..
Vance you can do mine too. I haven't lifted a shovel for the last 2 winters and don't plan to this year as long as there are neighbours like you.
Awesome Simon.  Looks like we'll be out and about on the ice around the first week of December, if not a bit sooner.  The sled comes out of hibernation next weekend!  Go get some crappies!
My lettuce died! Should have picked it Friday! Blower ready, scraper ready, snow shovel/melt ready, patio furniture packed away. what else can I do? take every Friday off.
Anybody hear a long term forecast for whats coming this winter to Ontario?
Cold and snow! Same as the last 50 years that I know of.
Just looked it up Forecast is for normal temps and higher than normal snowfall
4" on some backlakes here.   My buddies smashed Lakers today. So jealous.  I'm stuck unpacking and setting up the new house
I hear it's going to be a   "Micheal Jackson"  forecast for the winter.. Only wear 1 glove, because it might be warm, but on the other hand,  ??  lol..
